# Layer 0: Core Narrative + Style

narr:Narrative_1
  a narr:Narrative ;
  skos:note "The overarching narrative is that aswritten.ai can serve as a persistent, segmented organizational memory for a healthcare practice — capturing clinical knowledge, doctor relationships, training content, and business operations — while navigating HIPAA constraints through local deployment." .

narr:Narrative_2
  a narr:Narrative ;
  skos:note "Running LLMs locally on a practice server is framed both as a compliance workaround and as a differentiating premium feature for high-net-worth clientele." .

narr:Narrative_3
  a narr:Narrative ;
  skos:note "Recording training sessions, doctor calls, and clinical observations and feeding them into a memory system transforms ephemeral expertise into citable, searchable organizational knowledge." .

narr:Narrative_AswrittenValueProp
  a narr:Narrative ;
  skos:broader narr:WhatIsIt ;
  skos:note "Differentiated from a database by understanding decisions already made, current truth, and organizational direction. Premise: all documents are somewhat stale; the goal is identifying which part reflects direction." .

narr:Narrative_AuthorityPositioning
  a narr:Narrative ;
  skos:broader narr:CoreNarratives ;
  skos:note "Publishing a book and narrowing to defined specialties signals peer-level authority to physicians who respect specialty training." .

narr:Narrative_B2BReferralStrategy
  a narr:Narrative ;
  skos:broader narr:MarketContext ;
  skos:note "60-70% of referrals from MDs; remainder from PTs and concierge doctors. Upper West Side market characterized as having functionally infinite practitioners, patients, and budgets." .

narr:Narrative_DoctorReferralPipeline
  a narr:Narrative ;
  skos:broader narr:CoreNarratives ;
  skos:note "B2B doctor-to-doctor approach: doctors prescribe acupuncture care, removing the ethical burden of direct patient solicitation and increasing conversion." .

narr:Narrative_FranchiseLikeGrowth
  a narr:Narrative ;
  skos:broader narr:ExpansionPathway ;
  skos:note "Apprentices gain specialties; future locations can be spun out with founder blessing, creating aligned incentives." .

narr:Narrative_HIPAAComplianceJustification
  a narr:Narrative ;
  skos:note "Scarlet frames the enterprise tier not as an upsell but as a defensible compliance posture — 'more secure than HIPAA' requires infrastructure isolation features only available at the enterprise tier." .

narr:Narrative_LandAndExpand
  a narr:Narrative ;
  skos:broader narr:ExpansionPathway ;
  skos:note "Four core niches (post-stroke, pelvic floor, digestion, anxiety/depression) are the entry point; migraines and others are 'later sells'." .

narr:Narrative_ManagedCareShift
  a narr:Narrative ;
  skos:broader narr:StrategyOverview ;
  skos:note "Core business model innovation: patients receive a treatment plan from a senior practitioner, then see assistants for implementation, returning to the senior for review. Increases revenue while maintaining quality." .

narr:Narrative_NichePositioning
  a narr:Narrative ;
  skos:broader narr:PositioningThesis ;
  skos:note "Four niches: post-stroke recovery (Peter), pelvic floor care (Jordan), digestion (Peter), anxiety/depression (Peter)." .

narr:Narrative_PelvicFloorPitch
  a narr:Narrative ;
  skos:broader narr:ActorIncentiveAnalysis ;
  skos:note "Pitch to pelvic floor PTs: patients with central sensitization drop out of PT care; 3-5 acupuncture sessions regulate the nervous system, enabling PT completion. Win-win: PT gets paid, patient gets better." .

narr:Narrative_PostStrokeOpportunity
  a narr:Narrative ;
  skos:broader narr:MarketContext ;
  skos:note "Validated protocols call for 3 sessions/week, creating strong revenue cadence. Easy to pitch to doctors. Described as 'good money, good business, empty market.'" .

narr:Narrative_PricingTierBoundary
  a narr:Narrative ;
  skos:note "The core narrative is that the $400/month figure quoted on the onboarding call applies only to the Team Plan; enterprise-grade features (single-tenant, local LLM, zero data retention, segmented access, compliance) require the Enterprise Plan starting at $4,000/month. Transparency about this boundary is framed as a trust and compliance obligation given HIPAA context." .

narr:Narrative_TeamBasedCare
  a narr:Narrative ;
  skos:broader narr:OperatingModelShifts ;
  skos:note "Peter's evolving insight: best results come from teams; being part of a team means not trying to do everything the team does." .

narr:Narrative_TimeAsTheMoat
  a narr:Narrative ;
  skos:broader narr:CoreNarratives ;
  skos:note "Honest assessment: logistics and relationships are the primary barriers, not proprietary protocols." .

narr:Observation_Strategy_PositioningThesis
  a narr:Observation ;
  skos:broader narr:PositioningThesis ;
  skos:note "Meet doctors where they are: adopt specialty framing familiar to physicians rather than asking them to adopt holistic medicine framing." .

